âš™ï¸ Setup and Installation
Prerequisites

Python 3.9+

AWS CLI configured with valid credentials

Playwright dependencies installed

IAM permissions for Bedrock, S3, and CloudWatch

Installation Steps
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/utd-course-job-insight-agent.git
cd utd-course-job-insight-agent

# 2. Create and activate a virtual environment
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # For Mac/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate      # For Windows

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Install Playwright browser binaries
playwright install chromium

ğŸ§® Running the Agents Locally
a) Run the Job Market Agent
python3 Job_Market_Agent/main_job.py --s3 --s3-bucket nexai-job-market-data --aws-region us-east-1

b) Run the Course Catalog Agent
python3 Course_Catalog_Agent/utd_Trends_scrape.py --out-root data --no-headless

c) Launch AgentCore
agentcore invoke '{"inputText": "Show me UTD courses related to data analytics"}' --agent CourseMatchAI

